The Minister of Finance, Kemi Adeosun, says the federal government is making effort to ensure that the 10 million out-of-school children are enrolled. Mrs Adeosun who made this known, at the launch of the World Bank’s World Development Report 2018, with the theme: “Learning to Realise Education’s Promise’’ in Abuja said some key strategies are in place to improve the education system in Nigeria.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that according to the World Bank report, the quality of basic education remains low in a number of countries including Nigeria and globally, 125 million children are not acquiring functional literacy. Meanwhile, the Minister of Education, Adamu Adamu, said the country’s education policy was currently under review to effectively have an impact on students.  Also speaking, the World Bank Nigeria Country Director, Rachid Benmessaoud, reiterated the World Bank’s support for Nigeria in improving its education system.